Package interfaces

Interface iInventory

  • public interface iInventory
    Interface defining interactions with a game's inventory system. This interface includes methods to check for the presence of items, count items, find their positions, and interact with them in the inventory.

    • Method Detail

      • contains

        boolean contains​(java.lang.String[] itemIDs,
                 double threshold)
        Checks if the inventory contains any of the specified items, based on a threshold.
        Parameters:
        itemIDs - Array of item IDs to check in the inventory.
        threshold - The threshold value used for the check, threshold is a double where 1.0 represents 100% confidence. Usually above 0.80 (but often 0.90+).
        Returns:
        boolean indicating whether any of the specified items are present in the inventory.

      • contains

        boolean contains​(java.lang.String itemID,
                 double threshold)
        Checks if the inventory contains a specific item, based on a threshold.
        Parameters:
        itemID - The ID of the item to check in the inventory.
        threshold - The threshold value used for the check, threshold is a double where 1.0 represents 100% confidence. Usually above 0.80 (but often 0.90+).
        Returns:
        boolean indicating whether the specified item is present in the inventory.

      • count

        int count​(java.lang.String itemID,
          double threshold)
        Counts the quantity of a specific item in the inventory, based on a threshold.
        Parameters:
        itemID - The ID of the item to count in the inventory.
        threshold - The threshold value used for the count, threshold is a double where 1.0 represents 100% confidence. Usually above 0.80 (but often 0.90+).
        Returns:
        int representing the quantity of the specified item in the inventory.

      • itemPosition

        java.awt.Rectangle itemPosition​(java.lang.String itemID,
                                double threshold)
        Finds the position of a specific item in the inventory, based on a threshold.
        Parameters:
        itemID - The ID of the item whose position is to be found.
        threshold - The threshold value used for finding the item, threshold is a double where 1.0 represents 100% confidence. Usually above 0.80 (but often 0.90+).
        Returns:
        Rectangle representing the position of the specified item in the inventory.

      • tapItem

        void tapItem​(java.lang.String itemId,
             double threshold)
        Initiates a tap action on a specified item in the inventory, based on a threshold.
        Parameters:
        itemId - The ID of the item to be tapped.
        threshold - The threshold value used for identifying the item, threshold is a double where 1.0 represents 100% confidence. Usually above 0.80 (but often 0.90+).
